message.content: cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.LG. The paper focuses on question answering over knowledge graphs, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and database systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with database-related tasks such as entity detection, entity linking, and relation prediction, which suggest the sub-category cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.IR and cs.LG, respectively.
